<head>
<title>Family Guide Ratings</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<blockquote>
<center><h2>Family Guide Ratings</h2></center>
<br>
<center>
<img src="/townhall/townhall_shop/mrcstore/family1.gif">
</center>
<p>

<a name="perfect"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fyellow.gif"  alt="Yellow Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Almost Perfect</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(CBS/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Sunday 8:30 PM</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
A police detective and a TV producer attempt to juggle their relationship 
and the demands of their time-consuming careers.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><I><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
</FONT></I><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Although <I>Almost 
Perfect</I>'s scenarios are not explicit, it is implied that the 
unmarried protagonists are sexually active, and the moral ramifications 
of their affair are never addressed. The show has also characterized 
the religious as close-minded. <br></FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="gothic"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fyellow.gif"  alt="Yellow Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">American Gothic</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(CBS/drama)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Friday 10 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
An inherently evil sheriff employs demented methods to keep the 
peace in a small southern town.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Law enforcement is portrayed unfavorably. After a spate of publicity, 
<I>Gothic</I>'s producers complied with CBS' requests to tone 
down the violence in the series' controversial premiere; subsequent 
episodes have contained little or no violence. Occasional off-color 
language (&quot;bitch, &quot;piss&quot;) appears.<BR> 
</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="videos"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fgreen.gif"  alt="Green Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">America's Funniest 
Home Videos</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(ABC/reality)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Sunday 7 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Viewers send in home video footage in hopes of winning prize money 
for the funniest material.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Family-friendly show appropriate for viewers of all ages.<BR> 
</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="wanted"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fyellow.gif"  alt="Yellow Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">America's Most Wanted</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(Fox/reality)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Saturday 9:30 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
A reality-based show, <I>America's Most Wanted</I> presents dramatic 
recreations of crimes and descriptions of the suspects at large.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook">: 
Involves viewers in combating crime and puts positive spin on 
law enforcement. As is to be expected from this genre, the show 
contains violent imagery, and parents may consider it inappropriate 
for youngsters.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="90210"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fred.gif"  alt="Red Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Beverly Hills, 90210</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(Fox/drama)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Wednesday 8 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
A youth-targeted soap opera which revolves around a group of friends, 
most of whom are college juniors.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary: </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook">While 
extramarital sex is shown to have devastating effects, main characters 
regularly engage in premarital sex, and have yet to face any negative 
consequences. The soap has broadcast mixed messages on drugs -- 
while positive characters deride substance abuse, one regular 
continues to smoke marijuana without facing legal repercussions. 
The brightest note: a regular who vows to remain a virgin until 
her wedding night.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="house"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fyellow.gif"  alt="Yellow Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Bless This House</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(CBS/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Wednesday 8 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>Bless This House</I> centers on a mailman, his family, and 
their daily quest for a better life.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook">: 
Replete with smart-alec children and a promiscuous supporting 
character, <I>Bless This House'</I>s dialogue has included off-color 
language (&quot;sucks,&quot; &quot;ass,&quot; &quot;bastard&quot;). 
To its credit, the sitcom's views on matrimony are positive, and 
most discussions about sex are within the context of marriage.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="huntshow"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fgreen.gif"  alt="Green Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">The Bonnie Hunt Show</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(CBS/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Friday 8:30 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Set in Chicago, <I>Bonnie</I> <I>Hunt</I> features a single woman 
working for a television news program and her interactions with 
co-workers and quirky neighbors.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Unlike many sitcoms this season, the series doesn't resort to 
foul language or condone promiscuity. The importance of family 
and faith are frequently stressed.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="world"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fgreen.gif"  alt="Green Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Boy Meets World</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(ABC/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Friday 8:30 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Now in its third year, the show revolves around a young teen, 
his rebellious best friend, and his relationship with various 
family members.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Shows advocate sexual abstinence until marriage, and discuss the 
consequences of cheating on exams and lying. While the protagonist 
can be disrespectful, the parents and teachers always have the 
upper hand at the episode's end. The only downside: a recent instance 
of foul language (&quot;bite me&quot;).</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="love"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fgreen.gif"  alt="Green Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Brotherly Love</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(NBC/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Sunday 7 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background: </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook">A 
new family-oriented entry centering on an aspiring auto racer 
who helps run the family business after his father dies.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Generally a positive show with solid moral lessons about family 
loyalty; the main character learns that at least for the time 
being, his obligations to his younger brothers take precedence 
over his career and social life. Parents might find the show's 
mild sexual humor somewhat objectionable, given <I>Brotherly Love</I>'s 
early time slot and young target audience.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="hurrylove"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fred.gif"  alt="Red Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Can't Hurry Love</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(CBS/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Monday 8:30 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background: </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook">A 
young professional woman living in New York City searches, without 
success, for the perfect mate.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary: </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook">Premarital 
sex is not only endorsed, it is celebrated. Two regular characters 
are unabashedly promiscuous; their dialogue is often laced with 
sexual innuendo. Other characters have used foul language (&quot;ass,&quot; 
&quot;piss,&quot; &quot;suck&quot;).</FONT> 
 
 
<P> 
<a name="city"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fyellow.gif"  alt="Yellow Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Caroline in the City</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(NBC/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Thursday 9:30 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
The title character, a young woman residing in Manhattan, is a 
cartoonist whose work is distinctly autobiographical.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Caroline's sex life with her ex-boyfriend and her single neighbor's 
promiscuity have been condoned, as has the homosexual lifestyle. 
The show has used these issues as a backdrop for comedic dialogue, 
but has not resorted to vulgar humor &agrave; la <I>Roseanne</I>.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="west"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fred.gif"  alt="Red Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Central Park West</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(CBS/drama)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Wednesday 9 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
From the creators of <I>Melrose Place</I>, <I>Central Park</I> 
features young, hip New Yorkers attempting to cope with their 
fast-paced lives and careers. </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Another drama pushing the envelope in its use of nudity and vulgar 
language (&quot;bitch,&quot; &quot;ass&quot;), the show condones 
adultery and casual sex.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="hope"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fyellow.gif"  alt="Yellow Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Chicago Hope</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(CBS/drama)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Monday 10 PM</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>Chicago Hope</I> centers on the lives of doctors, nurses, and 
administrators of a prominent hospital.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Now in its second season, this series has been respectful of the 
religious, illustrated the merits of faith, and even-handedly 
presented all sides of the abortion issue. This season the show 
has demonstrated the drawbacks of single parenting.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="cleghorne"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fyellow.gif"  alt="Yellow Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Cleghorne!</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(WB/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Sunday 9:30 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>Cleghorne!</I> takes a comical look at the relationship between 
a single mother and her family living next door.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
While the sitcom showcases a less-than-traditional family arrangement, 
it repeatedly emphasizes the importance of a strong family unit. 
Although grace is said before meals, <I>Cleghorne!</I> has mocked 
one character's evangelical Christian beliefs. Dialogue has also 
contained some sexual innuendo. </FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="coach"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fyellow.gif"  alt="Yellow Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Coach</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(ABC/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Tuesday 9:30 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>Coach</I> features the head of a fictitious NFL expansion team, 
his family, and his assistant coaches.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>Coach</I>'s protagonist, a self-made man, regularly illustrates 
that hard work and dedication pay off. While the sitcom showcases 
a happy marriage, parents may find the show's permissive views 
on premarital sex unsuitable for younger viewers.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="cops"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fyellow.gif"  alt="Yellow Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Cops</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(Fox/reality)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Saturday 9 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>Cops</I> uses real-life footage of police officers from various 
cities apprehending criminals.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Law enforcement receives favorable treatment, although some footage 
is too violent for young viewing audiences.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="courthouse"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fred.gif"  alt="Red Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Courthouse</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(CBS/drama)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Wednesday 10 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
The personnel of a major city courthouse tackle the intricacies 
of law enforcement.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Most characters on <I>Courthouse</I> have been shown in sexual 
situations; adultery has been condoned and cohabitation has been 
endorsed. The gratuitous use of obscenities, graphic violence, 
and partial nudity in explicit sex scenes are prevalent. </FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="crew"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fred.gif"  alt="Red Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">The Crew</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(Fox/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Thursday 8:30 PM</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background: </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook">This 
new comedy series follows the adventures of a team of flight attendants 
based in Miami.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
The homosexual lifestyle of one character is not only countenanced, 
but is recurrent in every episode; tawdry sex jokes account for 
the vast majority of <I>The Crew</I>'s attempts at humor.</FONT> 
 
 
<P> 
<a name="cybill"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fred.gif"  alt="Red Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Cybill</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(CBS/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Sunday 8 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Cybill Shepherd plays a twice-divorced actress who is raising 
a teenage daughter and struggling with life's crises.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
This series is fraught with explicit discussions about sex and 
sexual innuendo. Marriage as an institution is frequently ridiculed 
by the show's characters, all of whom have had unsuccessful trips 
to the altar.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="davesworld"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fyellow.gif"  alt="Yellow Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Dave's World</FONT></B></I> 
<P><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(CBS/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Wednesday 8:30 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Based on the life of columnist Dave Barry, this sitcom features 
the antics of the writer and his family and friends.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary: </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook">Although 
<I>Dave's World</I> depicts family life favorably, parents might 
object to the show's sexual humor and somewhat suggestive dialogue.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="games"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fyellow.gif"  alt="Yellow Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Deadly Games</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(UPN/drama)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Tuesday 8 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
&quot;Deadly games&quot; ensue when a computer game comes to life 
and the show's main characters are forced to participate in each 
level of the game.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
This sci-fi drama offers no substantive social commentary; the 
villain regularly resorts to violence, although scenes are not 
explicitly gory.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="woman"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fgreen.gif"  alt="Green Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Dr. Quinn, Medicine 
Woman</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(CBS/drama)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Saturday 8 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
A period drama set in the late 1800s, <I>Dr. Quinn</I> features 
a woman doctor, her family, and the townspeople of Colorado Springs. 
</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
The series showcases an hour of predictably family-friendly viewing, 
featuring positive portrayals of the religious, marriage, and 
respect for parental authority. </FONT> 
 
