<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Sunday 9 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Three young career women strive for self-sufficiency.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><I><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
</FONT></I><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Although several 
episodes have implied approval for premarital sex, <I>First Time</I>'s 
visuals and dialogue have not been explicitly prurient. Marijuana 
use and disrespect for law enforcement have been countenanced. 
<BR> 
</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="frasier"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fyellow.gif"  alt="Yellow Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Frasier</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(NBC/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Tuesday 9 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
A multiple Emmy-winning hit that deals with a psychiatrist who 
hosts a radio call-in show, his family, and his co-workers.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Family responsibility is endorsed and law enforcement is portrayed 
favorably. <I>Frasier</I>'s humor is sophisticated in nature; 
sex jokes are infrequent and not rooted in vulgarity, and bedroom 
scenes are rare. More of a minus: one character, a woman, is unashamedly 
promiscuous.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="belair"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fgreen.gif"  alt="Green Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
