<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
This long-running sitcom features a teenager from a Philadelphia 
ghetto who is sent to live with his rich uncle's family in Bel-Air.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
A pro-family series,<I> Fresh Prince</I> continues to champion 
the work ethic, chastity, and individual responsibility. </FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="friends"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fred.gif"  alt="Red Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Friends</FONT></B></I> 
 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(NBC/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Thursday 8 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>Friends</I> centers on six Manhattanites who hang out with 
one another at home and at a coffee bar.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>Friends</I>' raciness has not been toned down with its move 
to 8 PM. This sitcom's gang of single twentysomethings discusses 
sex virtually every week; one male character in particular has 
had plenty of partners. Masturbation, oral sex, and homosexuality 
have been the focus of episodes. The show has also endorsed lesbian 
parenting. </FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="underfire"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fyellow.gif"  alt="Yellow Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Grace Under Fire</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(ABC/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Wednesday 9 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>Grace</I> follows the trials and tribulations a single mother 
faces when raising three children and trying to keep peace with 
her male co-workers at an oil refinery.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>Grace</I> does not glorify divorce and has reversed its initial 
cynicism about marriage, as evidenced by two happily married central 
characters. However, sexual innuendo permeates the dialogue, as 
does criticism of the devoutly religious.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="cooper"></a> 
