The last leg of ABC's family-friendly Friday-night lineup, <I>Hangin' 
</I>features a teacher who lives with his cousin, her young child, 
and a platonic female roommate.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
The sitcom has addressed family-friendly themes ranging from confronting 
schoolyard bullies to the importance of honesty. Educators receive 
positive portrayals as well.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="society"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fred.gif"  alt="Red Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">High Society</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(CBS/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Monday 9:30 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
A wealthy Manhattan publisher and her boozing novelist friend 
are at odds after the publisher takes in a friend going through 
a divorce.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
CBS' first midseason replacement, <I>High Society</I> has managed 
to extol premarital sex, deride marriage, champion the gay lifestyle, 
and showcase lewd humor, all within the scope of only two episodes.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="improvement"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fgreen.gif"  alt="Green Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Home Improvement</FONT></B></I> 
 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(ABC/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Tuesday 9 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
This series showcases the relationship between the protagonist, 
a cable TV host, his wife, and their three children.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
The Taylors, a secure family unit, stand out in television's landscape 
littered with atypical or dysfunctional families. The show's husband 
and wife work through everyday problems most couples face, coming 
away with a more secure marriage. They serve as positive role 
models to their children, teaching them about honesty, loyalty, 
and respect for parental authority. </FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="court"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fgreen.gif"  alt="Green Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">The Home Court</FONT></B></I> 
