<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Saturday 9:30 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
A family-court judge/single mother copes with family and work 
stress. </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>The Home Court</I> is thematically unobjectionable thus far. 
The judge has been admirably tough in her rulings, which often 
prove to be for society's benefit; less to viewers' benefit is 
the occasional rough language (&quot;piss,&quot; &quot;ass &quot;).</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="homicide"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fyellow.gif"  alt="Yellow Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Homicide: Life on 
the Street</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(NBC/drama)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Friday 10 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background: </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook">This 
critically acclaimed series focuses on the on-and-off-the-job 
pressures faced by a team of Baltimore homicide detectives. </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>Homicide</I> concentrates on solving murder cases; the show's 
implicit viewpoint is pro-police and tough on criminals. On occasion, 
the drama has also been critical of race-based hiring preferences. 
All violent content takes place off-camera, but the show's dark, 
disturbing undercurrents are not suitable for young viewers.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
