<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(Fox/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Thursday 8 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background: </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook">This 
sitcom focuses on four twentysomething women and two men who live 
in the same building.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
While <I>Living Single</I> avoids most controversial issues, episodes 
have promoted loyalty, honesty, and the importance of education. 
However, premarital sex is condoned.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="clark"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fgreen.gif"  alt="Green Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Lois &amp; Clark: 
The New Adventures of Superman</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(ABC/drama)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Sunday 8 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
A modern-day version of the <I>Superman</I> comic book series, 
<I>Lois &amp; Clark</I> features journalists Clark Kent, a.k.a. 
The Man of Steel, and his burgeoning romance with co-worker Lois 
Lane. </FONT> 
 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary: </FONT></B><I><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook">Superman</FONT></I><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
star Teri Hatcher aptly described this popular drama as &quot;the 
family show to watch.&quot; Scheduled against competing networks' 
racier sitcoms, the family-friendly <I>Lois and Clark</I> showcases 
a romantic, yet chaste relationship between the two lead characters 
and is obscenity-free. </FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="madaboutyou"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fyellow.gif"  alt="Yellow Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Mad About You</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(NBC/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Sunday 8 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Now in its fourth season, <I>Mad About You </I>features an upwardly 
mobile married couple.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>Mad About You</I> is adamantly pro-marriage, but is nonetheless 
an adult-oriented show. Parents should note its frankness about 
sexual matters and its off-color language (&quot;bite me,&quot; 
&quot;ass,&quot; &quot;piss&quot;).</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="married"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fred.gif"  alt="Red Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Married . . . with 
Children </FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(Fox/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Sunday 9 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background: </FONT></B><I><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook">Married...with 
Children</FONT></I><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">'s dysfunctional 
family is composed of an unsuccessful shoe salesman, his whining 
wife, their dim-witted daughter, and oversexed son.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:<I><B> 
</B></I></FONT></B><I><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Married</FONT></I><FONT 
SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
not only lacks family values, but routinely ridicules them. On 
virtually every episode the parents trade insults and are ridiculed 
by their progeny. Bathroom humor and scantily clad women are prevalent, 
as are lewd jokes centering on masturbation, promiscuity, and 
homosexuality.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="marshal"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fgreen.gif"  alt="Green Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">The Marshal</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(ABC/drama)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Monday 8 PM</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
Now in its second season, this drama follows a U.S. Marshal in 
his cross-country crime-fighting escapades.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>Marshal</I> is a positive reflection of law enforcement at 
its best; the title character always brings the villain to justice 
by the end of the show. A nice touch: the protagonist makes a 
point of spending time with his family in almost every episode.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="martin"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fred.gif"  alt="Red Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Martin</FONT></B></I><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
</FONT></B> 
<P> 
