<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Saturday 8 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>Martin</I> revolves around the life of a young radio disc jockey 
and his wife.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>Martin</I> has taken cheap shots at religion, featuring a lecherous 
preacher fleecing parishioners. Martin's sex-obsessed themes and 
dialogue are extremely suggestive for this timeslot; obscenities 
(&quot;ass,&quot; &quot;bitch&quot;) are prevalent.</FONT> 
 
 
<P> 
<a name="time"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fgreen.gif"  alt="Green Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Maybe This Time</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(ABC/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Saturday 8:30 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>Maybe</I> <I>This Time</I> stars Marie Osmond as a single mother 
and Betty White as a grandmother who are co-owners of  a cafe 
in small-town America.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
The mother and grandmother have disparate views about child-raising 
techniques, but ultimately agree on the merits of parental authority, 
honesty, and strict discipline.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="melrose"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fred.gif"  alt="Red Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Melrose Place</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(Fox/drama)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Monday 8 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
A prime time soap opera, <I>Melrose</I> features the relationships 
between a group of trendy young adults residing in a Los Angeles 
apartment complex.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary: </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook">Despite 
the show's early timeslot, <I>Melrose</I>'s patently steamy storylines 
have condoned adultery and promiscuity, addressed homosexuality, 
and endorsed abortion. Dialogue has featured vulgar language including 
&quot;bitch,&quot;  &quot;ass,&quot; and &quot;piss.&quot;</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="adjustments"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fgreen.gif"  alt="Green Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Minor Adjustments</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(NBC/comedy)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Sunday 7:30 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
A new series, <I>Minor Adjustments</I> focuses on a child psychologist 
who constantly deals with youngsters, both at work and at home.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
This series, which at times evokes <I>The Cosby Show</I>, is mostly 
wholesome -- the husband and wife have a happy marriage and clearly 
are devoted to their children. </FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">However, its occasionally 
questionable language (&quot;sucks&quot;) and a single allusion 
to premarital sex may be setting the stage for less- than-family-friendly 
themes in future installments.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
