FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
A woman from the other side of the tracks takes a job as a nanny 
for the three children of a successful Broadway producer.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
This light comedy steers clear of any controversial social issues, 
yet several instances of sexual innuendo have been written into 
the dialogue. Homosexuality has been used as a backdrop for humor, 
but the lifestyle was neither endorsed nor condemned.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="stacy"></a> 
