<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Thursday 9 PM</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
This police drama focuses on  street-smart detectives and the 
challenges they face on and off the job.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary: </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook">The 
show does present the repercussions of the absence of a two-parent 
household, but illegitimacy is nevertheless condoned. Several 
episodes contain violence, sexual content, and occasional obscenities. 
On the plus side, <I>New York Undercover</I> is pro-law-and-order 
and portrays police officers favorably.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="man"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fyellow.gif"  alt="Yellow Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">Nowhere Man</FONT></B></I> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">(UPN/drama)</FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Monday 9 PM</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background: </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook">A 
conspiracy-ridden fantasy, <I>Nowhere Man</I> revolves around 
a photographer whose identity is erased by unidentified authority 
figures attempting to silence dissent. Weekly episodes depict 
the protagonist's attempts to return to his former life.</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary: </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook">Sexual 
matters are treated casually. The drama's storylines, reminiscent 
of Oliver Stone's conspiracy tales, may mislead children: authority 
figures, including members of the military, are uniformly portrayed 
as evil. </FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="nypd"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fred.gif"  alt="Red Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
Schoolbook">NYPD Blue</FONT></B></I> 
