<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Wednesday 9 PM </FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Background:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
<I>Party of Five</I> features a family of five children suddenly 
orphaned after their parents die in an automobile accident. Several 
installments focus on difficulties experienced when children are 
without the stabilizing influence of parental discipline and wisdom. 
</FONT> 
<P> 
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">Summary:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 
FACE="Century Schoolbook"> 
The show regularly reinforces the desirability of a strong family 
unit. </FONT> 
<P> 
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Century Schoolbook">     However, <I>Party</I> 
continues to send mixed messages about matters of morality -- 
while one teen eschews premarital relations, two of her brothers 
are sexually active, and one has even moved his fiancee into the 
family's home.</FONT> 
 
<P> 
<a name="fences"></a> 
<img src="/mrc/images/fyellow.gif"  alt="Yellow Light"><I><B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Century 
