<TITLE>Montgomery Internship Program -- MRC</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<blockquote>
<center><h2> The Montgomery Internship Program</h2></center>

The MRC's Montgomery Internship Program, which is funded by benefactors
Mr. and Mrs. Gordon Montgomery, was established in 1992 with the
purpose of helping young conservatives in their pursuit to bring
balance to journalism.<BR>

<P>
 Interns at the MRC develop the ability to:<BR>

<P>
 <li> Identify bias in the national media.<BR>

<P>
<li> Conduct research tasks with the <a href="/mrc/news/">News</a> and <a href="/mrc/entertainment/">Entertainment</a> Research
Divisions, either at MRC headquarters or research sites within
the Washington D.C. area.<BR>

<P>
<li> Develop and strengthen writing skills by working one on one
with MRC   editorial staff on newsletters and special projects.
<BR>

<P>
<li> Conduct interviews with conservative leaders, and write about
their finding   in MRC newsletters.  <BR>

<P>
Internships are available for the Fall, Spring, or Summer semesters.
Those interested in the program are encouraged to apply early
due to the limited number of positions.  For more information complete the application below, or contact Christine Brookhart at the Media Research Center via phone (703-683-9733), fax (703-683-9736), email (cbrookhart@mediaresearch.org) or snail mail (113 S. West St. 2nd Floor, Alexandria, VA 22314). <BR>


